-//! Two-stage compressor detector: instant gain curve + GR smoothing.
+//! Peak-bridged 2-stage compressor detector.
 //!
-//! Architecture (DAFX textbook style):
-//! 1. Compute instantaneous level: 20*log10(|x|)
-//! 2. Apply gain curve (threshold/ratio/knee) → raw GR
-//! 3. Smooth the raw GR with asymmetric 1-pole (attack/release)
+//! Architecture:
+//! 1. Peak-bridge |input| with instant attack, slow fixed decay
+//!    → eliminates zero-crossing dips, gives stable amplitude estimate
+//! 2. Convert to dB: 20*log10(peak_level)
+//! 3. Apply gain curve → raw GR (stable, doesn't oscillate at audio rate)
+//! 4. Smooth raw GR with asymmetric 1-pole (user attack/release)
 //!
-//! This produces natural peak-weighted detection because the gain curve
-//! is nonlinear (soft knee). Averaging the nonlinear GR over a waveform
-//! cycle gives a result between peak and RMS detection, with the exact
-//! weighting controlled by the knee shape.
+//! The peak bridge prevents the asymmetric GR smoother from switching
+//! between attack/release coefficients every half-cycle, eliminating
+//! the Jensen's inequality duty-cycle bias.
 
